lyrics:
[verse]
Edwin, the brave, ventured out one night
To a hotpot dinner with delight
In his finest attire, he stepped inside
To savor flavors that would make him fly

[chorus]
Oh, Edwin, the connoisseur of feast
Hotpot delights, a grand culinary beast
Spices and broth, bubbling so divine
Edwin's taste buds on a journey, they align
